    "created_at": "2016-03-10T07:45:50Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-10T07:45:50Z",
    "body": "Chromium doesn't have good support for running two instances at the same time, most resources are guarded with file locks, like localStorage, so if you are using localStorage in one instance the accesses in other instances will be refused. And for resources that are not guarded by locks, race conditions might happen and it would be very bad.\n"
  },
